I'll write the fixed version:

```java
static Document parseByteData(ByteBuffer byteData, String charsetName, String baseUri, Parser parser) {
    String docData;
    Document doc = null;

    // Determine charset from meta if not provided
    if (charsetName == null) {
        // decode as UTF-8 first
        docData = Charset.forName(defaultCharset).decode(byteData).toString();
        doc = parser.parseInput(docData, baseUri);
        Element meta = doc.select("meta[http-equiv=content-type], meta[charset]").first();
        if (meta != null) {
            String foundCharset;
            if (meta.hasAttr("http-equiv")) {
                foundCharset = getCharsetFromContentType(meta.attr("content"));
                if (foundCharset == null && meta.hasAttr("charset")) {
                    try {
                        String candidate = meta.attr("charset");
                        if (Charset.isSupported(candidate)) {
                            foundCharset = candidate;
                        }
                    } catch (IllegalCharsetNameException e) {
                        foundCharset = null;
                    }
                }
            } else {
                foundCharset = meta.attr("charset");
            }

            if (foundCharset != null && foundCharset.length() != 0 && !foundCharset.equals(defaultCharset)) {
                foundCharset = foundCharset.trim().replaceAll("[\"']", "");
                charsetName = foundCharset;
                byteData.rewind();
                docData = Charset.forName(foundCharset).decode(byteData).toString();
                doc = null;
            }
        }
    } else {
        Validate.notEmpty(charsetName, "Must set charset arg to character set of file to parse. Set to null to attempt to detect from HTML");
        docData = Charset.forName(charsetName).decode(byteData).toString();
    }

    // Handle UTF-8 BOM indicator
    if (docData.length() > 0 && docData.charAt(0) == 65279) {
        byteData.rewind();
        String bomCharset = (charsetName != null) ? charsetName : defaultCharset;
        docData = Charset.forName(bomCharset).decode(byteData).toString();
        docData = docData.substring(1);
        charsetName = (charsetName != null) ? charsetName : defaultCharset;
    }

    if (doc == null) {
        doc = parser.parseInput(docData, baseUri);
        doc.outputSettings().charset(charsetName);
    }

    return doc;
}
```

This fix:
- In BOM check, use `charsetName` if not null, else `defaultCharset` for re-decoding.
- Do not override `charsetName` to `defaultCharset` unconditionally; keep it if already set.
- This prevents the bug where non-UTF-8 charset is overwritten by BOM handling.

Also, note that in the initial decode for null charset, we first decode as UTF-8, parse, then if meta found and different, re-decode. That's fine.

